// Adversarial: DamageBoost(0.5) is applied inside Until(TimeExpires(1.0)) on every Bumped
// event. The Until wrapper must fire the boost immediately and schedule a reversal after
// 1.0 seconds. If the reversal message fails — or if multiple concurrent Until timers each
// queue a reversal and one is dropped — ActiveDamageBoosts grows unboundedly and
// the damage multiplier diverges from the expected single-boost value.
// Dense layout drives frequent bumps to create many overlapping Until windows.
// BoltSpeedAccurate is included as a secondary signal: a corrupted damage multiplier can
// indirectly affect bolt physics in systems that gate on damage state. 5000 frames gives
// multiple Until cycles (each 1.0 s at 64 fps ≈ 64 frames) to expire and restart.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.5)),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltSpeedAccurate, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 1984,
    initial_effects: [
        On(target: Bolt, then: [
            When(trigger: Bumped, then: [
                Until(trigger: TimeExpires(1.0), then: [
                    Do(DamageBoost(0.5)),
                ]),
            ]),
        ]),
    ],
)
